entries.title: 'The enemy is always looking for us': Hidden in the forest, Ukraine's drone operators are crucial to eastern battle
entries.description: The pine forests near the city of Kreminna have become one of the hottest combat zones in the war in eastern Ukraine. Almost every weapon seems to be at work here, artillery, howitzers, tanks and mortars. But perhaps the most important is the smallest: The reconnaissance drone.

entries.title: Bolsonaro seeks six-month US tourist visa
entries.description: Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro is seeking a six-month tourist visa to remain in the United States, the law firm representing Bolsonaro confirmed to CNN Brasil on Monday.

entries.title: Asia's richest man is uncomfortably in the crosshairs of a tiny US research firm
Why everyone is talking about Andrea Riseborough's Oscar campaign
entries.description: Andrea Riseborough may not be a name that rings many bells for the average moviegoer.

entries.title: A dire forecast: Scientists used AI to find planet could cross critical warming threshold sooner than expected
entries.description: The planet could cross critical global warming thresholds sooner than previous models have predicted, even with concerted global climate action, according to a new study using machine learning.

entries.title: With a finch and a fish, this scientist has changed our understanding of the tree of life
entries.description: On the Galapagos Islands, a ground finch that usually munched on small, soft seeds was forced, during a drought, to eat harder, larger ones.

entries.title: Prospect for passing policing legislation in Congress remains low
entries.description: The prospect for new bipartisan negotiations on Capitol Hill for legislation overhauling policing laws remains very low, despite calls from the NAACP, the Congressional Black Caucus and others for congressional action in the wake of the brutal police beating and death of Tyre Nichols.

entries.title: The battle in eastern Ukraine has been 'constant,' as Russian paratroopers now target a key highway, one of Kyiv's commanders told Ukrainian TV
Priscilla Presley is contesting validity of Lisa Marie Presley's will
entries.description: Priscilla Presley is challenging the validity of her late daughter Lisa Marie Presley's will.

entries.title: NASA orbiter captures image of a bear's face on Mars
entries.description: As a NASA orbiter turned its camera to the Martian surface, the face of a bear seemed to be looking back.

entries.title: 4-foot-long snake beats the heat by hiding out in an inconvenient place
entries.description: A snake catcher in Australia calmly removed the tree snake after a man found it in his toilet.

entries.title: Hockey Hall of Famer and Stanley Cup champion Bobby Hull has died at 84
entries.description: Bobby Hull, hockey Hall of Famer and Stanley Cup champion, died Monday at 84, the Chicago Blackhawks announced.

entries.title: This unique Giacometti chandelier was bought for $309. It's now expected to sell for millions
entries.description: A chandelier bought for just £250 ($309) from a London antique store looks set to sell for millions at an auction at Christie's.

entries.title: Ex-publisher of National Enquirer set to meet with prosecutors investigating Trump
entries.description: David Pecker, the former head of the company that publishes the National Enquirer, is expected to meet with Manhattan prosecutors investigating former President Donald Trump, people familiar with the matter said, indicating the probe is escalating.

entries.title: Audi's new concept vehicle is two cars in one. See it in action
entries.description: Audi's Activesphere is an electric concept vehicle that uses augmented reality to give its passengers layers of information and can operate fully autonomously

entries.title: US skier Kyle Smaine killed in avalanche in Japan aged 31
entries.description: US skier Kyle Smaine has died in an avalanche in Japan aged 31, according to a post from his wife on Instagram.

entries.title: Barrett Strong, Motown singer and songwriter, dead at 81
entries.description: Barrett Strong, the voice and songwriter behind Motown Record's first hit, has died, according to a post from The Motown Museum.

entries.title: More than 500 US flights canceled as winter weather moves in
entries.description: More than 500 US flights have been canceled on Monday as winter weather bears down on a wide swath of the United States.

entries.title: Woman rides out tornado with her grandson in the car. Her dashcam captured the terrifying moments
entries.description: Video taken by a dashboard camera during a tornado in Pasadena, Texas, shows the harrowing moments a woman, her daughter and grandson spent trapped in their vehicle as the twister passed. CNN affiliate KHOU has more.

entries.title: See Lisa Loring play the original Wednesday Addams
entries.description: The actress, best known as the first to play Wednesday Addams in the original "The Addams Family" sitcom has died at the age of 64, according to her longtime agent.

entries.title: Ashley Judd says she needed to go back into therapy after seeing her mother's death scene in media
entries.description: Ashley Judd says she had to re-enroll herself in trauma therapy to cope with the recent media coverage of her mother's death.

entries.title: Blinken visit reaches new urgency as Israeli, Palestinian tensions boil
entries.description: US Secretary of State Antony Blinken's trip to Israel and the West Bank may have been in the works for weeks, but it couldn't come at a more pressing time.

entries.title: Patrick Mahomes and Jalen Hurts to be first Black quarterbacks to face off at the Super Bowl
entries.description: The matchup between the Kansas City Chiefs and Philadelphia Eagles will be the first in Super Bowl history to feature two Black starting quarterbacks, as Patrick Mahomes and Jalen Hurts bid to lead their teams to glory on the biggest stage of all.

entries.title: Straight out of a Hollywood script, actor Ryan Reynolds watches Wrexham draw thrilling FA Cup encounter
entries.description: As the saying goes, it's the hope that kills you as a soccer fan -- just ask Ryan Reynolds.

entries.title: Man rescued after crashing stolen police car on train tracks
entries.description: Atlanta police officers rescued a man, who had stolen a patrol car, seconds before the train struck the vehicle.

entries.title: Boris Johnson claims Putin threatened him
entries.description: Former British Prime Minister Boris Johnson claims in an upcoming BBC documentary that Russian President Vladimir Putin threatened him with a missile. CNN correspondent Clare Sebastian has more.

entries.title: Ilia Malinin: 18-year-old 'quadgod' wins first US figure skating championships title
entries.description: Teenager Ilia Malinin won his first US figure skating championships title on Sunday, even though he was unable to nail his ambitious free skate program.

entries.title: Ryanair is making record profits as booming demand sends airfares soaring
entries.description: Ryanair expects it will be able to charge higher prices for flights over Easter and the summer, thanks to strong demand from American and Asian tourists and less competition from rivals.

entries.title: Former New Zealand rugby player Campbell Johnstone becomes first All Black to come out as gay
entries.description: Former New Zealand rugby player Campbell Johnstone became the first All Black to come out publicly as gay, in an interview with TVNZ's Seven Sharp on Monday.

entries.title: Here's why you should always wait for the earnings call
entries.description: Investors are pretty bad at living in the moment. We're currently in the thick of fourth quarter earnings reports, but traders don't seem to care about how companies fared during the final months of 2022. They're more focused on what's going to happen in the future.

entries.title: TikTok CEO to testify before Congress in March
entries.description: TikTok CEO Shou Zi Chew will testify at an upcoming hearing before the House Energy and Commerce Committee, a committee spokesperson confirmed to CNN Monday.

entries.title: Marie Kondo is focusing on what's important -- and that means letting the tidying slide
entries.description: Queen of clean Marie Kondo admits that tidying up is no longer top of her to-do list..

entries.title: 'A new era of accountability.' What Memphis got right after the death of Tyre Nichols
entries.description: Weeks after Tyre Nichols was brutalized by Memphis police officers, city law enforcement officials are being hailed for their unusually rapid investigation and transparency compared to similar cases in other US cities.

entries.title: Israel was behind drone attacks at military plant in Iran, US media report
entries.description: US officials believe drone attacks at a military plant in Iran's central city of Isfahan were carried out by Israel, according to US media reports.

entries.title: Gucci names Sabato De Sarno as new creative director
entries.description: Gucci has named fashion designer Sabato De Sarno as its new creative director, ending months of speculation about who would take on one of fashion's most coveted roles.

entries.title: NBA referees admit to 'gut-wrenching' mistake in Lakers-Celtics game as Dennis Schröder calls for officials to be fined
entries.description: The fallout from the egregious no-call in the final second of Saturday's game between the Los Angeles Lakers game and the Boston Celtics shows no sign of ending, with the official NBA Referees Twitter account admitting to the error on Sunday

entries.title: WHO says Covid-19 remains a global health emergency, but pandemic is at a 'transition point'
entries.description: Covid-19 remains a global health emergency, the World Health Organization said on Monday, but it acknowledged the pandemic is at a "transition point."

entries.title: Norway discovers huge trove of metals, minerals and rare earths on its seabed
entries.description: A Norwegian study has found a "substantial" amount of metals and minerals ranging from copper to rare earths on the seabed of its extended continental shelf, authorities said on Friday in their first official estimates.

entries.title: Everything that happened at Haute Couture Week 2023
entries.description: While temperatures in Paris hit below or near freezing, editors, celebrities and influencers wrapped themselves up in balaclavas, blanket scarves and big coats ready for one of the most opulent affairs on the fashion calendar: Haute Couture Week.

entries.title: Donna Kelce becomes first mother to have two sons play against each other in the Super Bowl
entries.description: Seeing your children succeed is what every parent wants. But for Donna Kelce, the success of both her sons will provide a conflict of interest.

entries.title: Lisa Loring, original Wednesday Addams actress, dead at 64
entries.description: Lisa Loring, best known as the first actress to play Wednesday Addams in the original "The Addams Family" sitcom, has died at the age of 64.

entries.title: 'I'm just here for the comments': Empire State Building riles New Yorkers after celebrating Super Bowl-bound Philadelphia Eagles' win
entries.description: The Empire State Building was lit in green and white to celebrate the Philadelphia Eagles' victory in the NFC Championship game on Sunday -- a decision that's sparked a bit of a backlash in the Big Apple.

entries.title: Blast in mosque in Pakistan kills at least 25 people, with scores injured
entries.description: A blast inside a mosque in Pakistan's northwestern city of Peshawar on Monday has left at least 17 people dead and 83 more injured, according to Mohammad Aijaz Khan, Peshawar police chief.

entries.title: Novak Djokovic says he 'emotionally collapsed' after Australian Open win
entries.description: For almost two decades, we have become accustomed to Novak Djokovic winning grand slams. But seeing the world No. 1 sobbing on the floor as he celebrated his Australian Open victory with his family and team was a first. He would later say he had "emotionally collapsed."

entries.title: Renault will slash stake in Nissan as they overhaul their alliance
entries.description: Carmakers Renault and Nissan have agreed to restructure their longstanding partnership, with the French company whittling down its stake in the Japanese firm to 15%.

entries.title: The family of five flying around the world in a tiny plane
entries.description: Spending over a year flying around the world with your family in a tiny single-engine aircraft is something most people could only imagine.

entries.title: Human and chimpanzee teens share similar struggles, study says. But your teen may be less patient
entries.description: Chimpanzee teens may not be so different from the ones living in our homes, a new study says.

entries.title: Blackouts killed thousands of his chickens. Hear why this farmer is furious
entries.description: Last year, South Africa saw power blackouts on more than 200 days. The disruptive energy crisis is putting everyday life as well as the hopes and dreams of millions at risk. CNN's David McKenzie reports.

entries.title: This 136-year-old London coffee store doesn't need to move with the times
entries.description: There's a certain nostalgia that clings to London's Soho; "it's not what it once was" is an almost constant refrain. Carnaby Street, famous for its nonconformist fashion in the Swinging Sixties, is now filled with chain stores. Many of the area's most insalubrious haunts are long gone, and in their place mostly restaurants, which come and go. The pace of change is rapid and not all change is bad.

entries.title: New Zealand's biggest city braces for more heavy rains after deadly floods
entries.description: New Zealand authorities warned Monday that the situation in flood-hit Auckland was likely to worsen after "unprecedented" rainfall brought devastating floods that have killed at least four people and forced hundreds to evacuate in the country's largest city.

entries.title: The disappearance of a teen gripped China. The discovery of his body raised more questions
entries.description: For three months, the disappearance of Hu Xinyu gripped China.

entries.title: Korean star Song Joong-ki announces marriage to Katy Louise Saunders, says they are expecting a baby
entries.description: South Korean actor Song Joong-ki married British actress Katy Louise Saunders Monday and the two are expecting a child, Song's agency, HighZium Studio, told CNN.

entries.title: 'Attack on India:' Adani slams US short seller over fraud allegations
entries.description: Adani Group has published a detailed rebuttal running to more than 400 pages against allegations of fraud made by a US investment firm, calling the short seller's investigation of the ports-to-power conglomerate "a calculated attack on India."

entries.title: An 'extremely dangerous' kidnapping suspect has evaded capture for nearly a week, prompting police to call for the public's help
entries.description: A sweeping multi-day manhunt continues for a suspect accused of brutally beating and kidnapping a woman in Oregon who remains in critical condition, according to police.

entries.title: Virginia school announces new safety protocols as students return to class nearly a month after a 6-year-old allegedly shot a teacher
entries.description: Richneck Elementary School has announced new safety protocols as students return to classes on Monday, nearly a month after a 6-year-old student allegedly shot his teacher inside a classroom.

ASML says 'rules are being finalized' on chip export controls to China
entries.description: ASML, a Dutch maker of semiconductor equipment, says "rules are being finalized" on export controls, amid reports that the Netherlands and Japan have joined the United States in restricting sales of some computer chip machinery to China.

entries.title: NATO secretary general urges South Korea to allow direct arms exports to Ukraine
entries.description: NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg on Monday asked South Korea to reconsider its rule on not exporting weapons to countries in conflict so it could help arm Ukraine in repelling Russia's invasion.

entries.title: Ukraine is relying on Soviet-era tanks until Western reinforcements
entries.description: Dug in amid the rolling hills west of Bakhmut, the tanks of the Ukrainian army's 28th Mechanized Brigade are helping to hold the line against a growing Russian offensive.

entries.title: Analysis: How Russia misread Germany's growing influence
entries.description: Two years ago, Moscow eyed a US-German standoff over the Nord Stream 2 gas pipeline as a litmus test of transatlantic power.

entries.title: US zoo will let you name a cockroach after an ex and feed it to an animal
entries.description: The San Antonio Zoo is offering a special Valentine's Day greeting for exes who just won't bug off.

entries.title: 'The Last of Us' just made an early claim to one of the best TV episodes of 2023
entries.description: If the hoopla surrounding "The Last of Us" has felt at all excessive through the first two episodes, the third chapter of the HBO series lives up to the weight of all the hype, laying early claim to what will almost inevitably be discussed as one of the best hours of television in 2023.

entries.title: GOP oversight committee member pressed on investigating Biden over Trump
entries.description: CNN's Pamela Brown asks House Oversight Committee member Rep. James Comer (R-KY) about how the committee will handle separate investigations into the management of classified documents by President Joe Biden and former president Donald Trump.

entries.title: Eagles crush 49ers, Chiefs nip Bengals to set up Super Bowl LVII matchup
entries.description: The Kansas City Chiefs are advancing to Super Bowl LVII following a 23-20 victory over the Cincinnati Bengals in the AFC Championship game on Sunday at Arrowhead Stadium in Kansas City, Missouri.

entries.title: DeSantis is backing down from a fight with Trump
entries.description: "I pity the fool who runs against President Trump," failed GOP Arizona gubernatorial candidate Kari Lake tweeted this weekend as the former President kicked off his first 2024 presidential campaign event.
